1615
01:12:02.665 --> 01:12:05.125
and that is the rabbit nuisance act of 1881.

1616
01:12:06.045 --> 01:12:07.565
European settlers introduced rabbits

1617
01:12:07.565 --> 01:12:09.005
to New Zealand in the 1830s,

1618
01:12:09.015 --> 01:12:12.485
which soon became a major agricultural pest in response

1619
01:12:12.485 --> 01:12:14.005
to the importation of muids.

1620
01:12:14.305 --> 01:12:16.245
In this case, stokes weasels

1621
01:12:16.245 --> 01:12:19.365
and ferrets was widely advocated as a means of control.

1622
01:12:19.435 --> 01:12:21.605
Despite the warnings of prominent naturalists

1623
01:12:22.095 --> 01:12:24.165
after initial support and earlier bills seeking

1624
01:12:24.165 --> 01:12:26.685
to ban the importation of Muids was defeated.

1625
01:12:26.745 --> 01:12:28.045
In 1876,

1626
01:12:28.495 --> 01:12:30.925
after part persistent lo uh, lobbying,

1627
01:12:30.925 --> 01:12:33.765
the rabbit nuisance bill of 1881 was drafted.

1628
01:12:33.765 --> 01:12:36.685
This bill proposed protections for enemies of the rabbits

1629
01:12:37.195 --> 01:12:39.285
keen to clear land for agrarian reform.

1630
01:12:39.345 --> 01:12:41.685
The executive introduced the bill hot on the heels

1631
